Title: An Icy Heart
Author: Dust_And_Shadows
Genre: anna, elsa, elsanna, fanfic, frozen, girlxgirl
Summary: Elsa is a orphan who jumps from foster home to foster home, and her parents died in a mysterious fatal accident when she was three. She always seems to get in trouble, even though she always tries to be good. It's not her fault that things happen to her....well, not intentionally anyway. Elsa is depressed and it's getting worse because of Alexia, a bully at her new school.  One day a girl named Anna is transferred to Elsa's homeroom. Since then, Elsa's been tormenting herself with thoughts of Anna.   Anna's family is anything but perfect. Her dad left them when she was five years old, right after Kristoff was born. Anna has a lot of pressure from her mom for her to do good in school to earn a scholarship. Her relationship with her boyfriend, Hans, is screwed up too. Hans always cheats on her, but she keeps letting him come back. As a well-known freshman in high school, the pressure never ends.  Can Anna and Elsa help each other survive freshman year and (maybe) help solve each other's problems? Or will Anna keep coming back to Hans and Elsa fall further into depression?      Disclaimer: All characters are not my own, they are owned by Disney and/or Dreamworks unless specified. Other characters not owned by Disney are my own, so no stealing please!    ***If you do not like reading about depressed and/or lesbian/gay/bi/etc people, you most likely won't want to read my story. Please don't comment mean/rude things, depressed people and gays have feelings just like you (sorry to be rude, but duh). Please don't be ignorant of that***

Genre: disneycrossover, disneymodernday, dramatic, elsanna, elsannafandom, elsannaship, elsaofarendelle, frozenfanfic, frozenfanfiction, olafthesnowman
Summary: After the loss of their mother and simultaneous disappearance of their father, Olaf and Elsa are orphaned siblings, doing everything they can to keep each other alive (...and sane). With the assistance of their older cousin, Kristoff, they are able to maintain a somewhat peaceful and calm lifestyle. However, upon registering for classes for the upcoming semester, Kristoff and Elsa face a new problem: no one can pick up Olaf from school. Elsa and Kristoff then reluctantly decide to find a babysitter for their adorable, favorite, summer loving 5th grader.  After ages of interviewing nightmare babysitters, Kristoff and Elsa come to discover a young, spunky, senior high schooler named Anna, who appears more than enthusiastic to do the job while Olaf immediately approves of Anna taking the position. However, Elsa can't help but feel that there's something familiar about the red head. In this story, you can look forward to heart warming moments of friendship, drama, emotional roller coasters, mixed feelings, possibly tears and of course, Elsanna.
